    "title": "Crossing Over",
    "description": "&quot;A short saying often contains much wisdom.&quot;\n– Sophocles\n\n&quot;I can tell you that it is no game for children, and I will confess that, in spite of my nine campaigns, I felt myself turn pale when the first ball flashed past me.&quot; \n– Arthur Conan Doyle, on the game of &quot;cricket&quot;. \n\n&quot;I am prepared to concede without further argument that all the theoretical constructions, including geometry, which are used in the various branches of physics are only imperfect instruments to enable the world of empirical fact to be reconstructed in our minds.&quot; \n– Richard von Mises\n\n&quot;If we wished to relate the space of the [Cubist] painters to geometry, we should have to refer it to the non-Euclidean mathematicians; we should have to study, at some length, certain of Riemann's theorems.&quot; \n– Jean Metzinger",
